NEW YORK (AP) — Orlando Magic guard Cole Anthony has been fined $25,000 by the NBA for directing profane and derogatory remarks toward a game official.Byron Spruell, the president of league operations, announced the fine on Friday.The incident occurred at the conclusion of Orlando’s 111-102 loss to the Los Angeles Clippers on Wednesday night at Amway Center.The Magic (9-40) have endured a frustrating season, and own the NBA’s worst record.Orlando hosts the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.___More AP NBA: https://apnews.com/hub/NBA and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports